    <item>
      <title>Docs: Configuração do Robolectric</title>
      <link>https://zupit.github.io/docs-beagle/pt/docs/tutoriais/testes/configura%C3%A7%C3%A3o-do-robolectric/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://zupit.github.io/docs-beagle/pt/docs/tutoriais/testes/configura%C3%A7%C3%A3o-do-robolectric/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;o-que-é&#34;&gt;O que é?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;O Roboletric é um &lt;strong&gt;framework para testes unitários&lt;/strong&gt; no Android. Uma de suas funções é simular informações  sobre o contexto do Android durante a realização desses testes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Antes de utilizá-lo, é preciso configurar uma dependência do Yoga Layout chamada de &lt;strong&gt;SoLoader&lt;/strong&gt; que, se não estiver habilitado para &lt;strong&gt;modo TESTE&lt;/strong&gt;, vai ocorrer um erro de &lt;strong&gt;nullPointerException&lt;/strong&gt;, uma vez que a view não existirá naquele contexto.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-info&#34; role=&#34;alert&#34;&gt;

Vale lembrar que o Beagle utiliza &lt;strong&gt;Yoga Layout&lt;/strong&gt; para &lt;a href=&#34;../../features/layout-de-componentes/&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;posicionar os componentes na tela&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sendo assim, você precisa configurar o nosso SDK para ativar o &amp;ldquo;TesteMode&amp;rdquo; no SoLoader quando iniciar um teste e desativá-lo assim que terminar. Para tal, basta utilizar as funções conforme indicado a seguir.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;como-configurar&#34;&gt;Como configurar?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para configurar o Beagle  para os testes do &lt;strong&gt;Roboeletric&lt;/strong&gt;, adicione o código abaixo no seu caso de teste:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-kotlin&#34; data-lang=&#34;kotlin&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#5c35cc;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;@BeforeClass&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#204a87;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;setup&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;BeagleSdk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;setInTestMode&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span style=&#34;color:#5c35cc;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;@AfterClass&lt;/span&gt; 
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#204a87;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;teardown&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;BeagleSdk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;deinitForTest&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      </description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Docs: Usando widget Id</title>
      <link>https://zupit.github.io/docs-beagle/pt/docs/tutoriais/testes/usando-widget-id/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://zupit.github.io/docs-beagle/pt/docs/tutoriais/testes/usando-widget-id/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para testar sua aplicação, você precisa de um Widget ID. Para fazer isso, Beagle oferece alguns métodos &lt;strong&gt;set&lt;/strong&gt; e &lt;strong&gt;get.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nessa seção, você verá dois específicos:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Set Id&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Get Id&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;set-id&#34;&gt;Set Id&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;O método Set Id é usado quando você precisa setar um Id no &lt;a href=&#34;../../api/widget.md&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;widget&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fornecido para o &lt;a href=&#34;../../principais-conceitos.md#backend-for-frontend&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BFF&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Para fazer isso, você precisa chamar esse método no widget que você quer o Id setado durante o momento que você está criando o seu widget.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Veja como funciona abaixo:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-kotlin&#34; data-lang=&#34;kotlin&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;Text&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;text&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Text with id&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;setId&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;myTextId&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;get-id&#34;&gt;Get Id&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No Get Id, você tem diferentes maneiras de setar de acordo com a sua plataforma frontend.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Veja abaixo:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No Android para obter um Widget Id você precisa chamar a &lt;code&gt;String.toAndroidId()&lt;/code&gt; e esse método retornará um Id para você usar onde precisar.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Veja como funciona, abaixo:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-kotlin&#34; data-lang=&#34;kotlin&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;myTextId&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;toAndroidId&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;No iOS, o Id é registrado no &lt;code&gt;accessibilityIdentifier&lt;/code&gt;. Com isso, para usá-lo, você precisa usar o mesmo valor que está no &lt;code&gt;setId()&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Veja como funciona, abaixo:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-swift&#34; data-lang=&#34;swift&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#4e9a06&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;myTextId&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Na Web, existe uma configuração default que cada componente renderizado pelo Beagle recebe o &amp;lsquo;data-beagle-id&amp;rsquo; que está em html, se o backend não setar o Id.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Se você quiser recuperar, use o javascript e html rodando o comando abaixo:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-javascript&#34; data-lang=&#34;javascript&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;element&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;getAttribute&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000&#34;&gt;widgetId&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#000;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;O valor do Widget Id será personalizado, se o backend setar o Id (como no exemplo, &amp;ldquo;myTextId&amp;rdquo;) ou ele será um valor default  (&amp;lsquo;data-beagle-id&amp;rsquo;).&lt;/p&gt;

      </description>
